javac *.java

jar -cf tunnel.jar *.class

jar -umf mainClassInfo tunnel.jar


where mainClassInfo contains the one line

	Main-Class: TcpTunnelGui
	
Then you can execute TcpTunnelGui via the command line

	java -jar TcpTunnelGui listenOnThisPort targetServerDomainName targetServerPort
	
eg

	java -jar TcpTunnelGui 8888 jcbServer.uwaterloo.ca 80
	
Note that you can't listen on port 80 on a unix machine unless you're root,
which is why this example listens on port 8888.

To change the size in which text passing through this tool is displayed on the screen,
change the value of the variable mainPanelTextSize in TcpTunnelGui.java, recompile, and run.

For details on packaging jar files, see

	http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/jar/basics/index.html
    http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/jar/basics/mod.html